{"lemma":"حَسِيباتٌ","slug":"حَسِيباتٌ","root":"ح.س.ب","root_slug":"ح-س-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-س-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَسِيب","root":"حسب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7950"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"All Sufficient (God)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"highborn, noble"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb حَسُبَ (ḥasuba)."},"ipa":["/ħa.siːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7950","headword_ar":"حَسِيبٌ","root":"Hsb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A reckoner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taker of accounts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAsibN","text_ar":"حَاسِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sufficer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"giver of what is sufficient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHosaba","text_ar":"اَحْسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufoEilN","text_ar":"مُفْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It has the former of these significations, or the latter, in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafaY biA@ll~`hi HasiybFA","text_ar":"كَفَى بِا@للّٰهِ حَسِيبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is sufficient as a reckoner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a giver of what sufficeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Fr, K, TA,) in the Kur [iv. 7, and xxxiii. 39]: (TA:) and so in the Kur iv. 88. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasiybuka A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"حَسِيبُكَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) in the L"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasobuka","text_ar":"حَسْبُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [both of which phrases are used in the present day in the sense here following,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"execute, vengeance upon thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"punish thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) meaning an imprecation though literally predicatory. (IAmb, Har p. 371.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusobaAnuka EalaY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"حُسْبَانُكَ عَلَى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasaba","text_ar":"حَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Characterized,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguished, by what is termed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasabN","text_ar":"حَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as explained above"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous, liberal, honourable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a numerous household:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusabaA='u","text_ar":"حُسَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","K","TA","S","L","Msb","Az","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}